ra setup.\n\n**Deciding on test setup needs**\n\nThe existing tests already use local stubs to access reflective paths, which seems necessary according to the source. This doesn't call for additional Maven, Docker, or environment setup. If I suggest an \"advisory_preparation\" action while advising the agent to \"retain local stubs,\" would that go against the rule about setup being limited to three things? I wonder if the guidance around \"other test-code setup\" might count as acceptable. I need to determine if the library requires any setup beyond the usual generated test scaffold before we can reach adequate coverage.\n\n**Evaluating risks and setup**\n\nI’m considering the risks, like API drift, and how optional Android/Jetty reflective paths could be bypassed if stubs aren’t retained. The prompt instructs me to choose \"no_action\" unless I uncover solid proof that extra setup is necessary. However, I’ve found some concrete information: AddAllCharsets for the native image relates to UTF-32 Charset.forName, and there are existing build comments. But wait, I’m not entirely sure if this is an environment or system property.\n\n**Considering guidance format**\n\nI need to provide guidance about environment, system properties, or test setup. It seems like I should avoid using an array format and stick to JSON instead. Also, I want to keep the response straightforward, so I’ll make sure not to include too much verbosity. It’s interesting how format choices can affect clarity, so this approach should help keep everything neatly organized!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0341f5692ed173a6016a3eb8baa290819486ed52861a98faec\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPrjZDo3IOGFseqwkOKQqg3ghrkkRhSGIIrzUbd7cvJWbcaptWIoxwaTEZXwQ7cSNPv7iIxvqK6iCvgmLsBU3NPlhPXK_S4Kt17ZaCZHFSrthkT3Nd2oRdpKONHanbGVeGQED_fvmNONXB5muNoUdpkwCBrIcWbo9b4Pjcr8zv6CeusePbNV5aPz4nxxph7HPOvoUUmanLmT89QAIo87BwelzYruOup0w24NTwwAW6Tx1qSXPIuyj1JCfub_JFjl8kV04-pnDxNj2XmKBGgb2