However, should I suggest an advisory preparation action based on the guidance? It seems I need clarity on the extra setup.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Deciding on test setup needs**\\n\\nThe existing tests already use local stubs to access reflective paths, which seems necessary according to the source. This doesn't call for additional Maven, Docker, or environment setup. If I suggest an \\\"advisory_preparation\\\" action while advising the agent to \\\"retain local stubs,\\\" would that go against the rule about setup being limited to three things? I wonder if the guidance around \\\"other test-code setup\\\" might count as acceptable. I need to determine if the library requires any setup beyond the usual generated test scaffold before we can reach adequate coverage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating risks and setup**\\n\\nI’m considering the risks, like API drift, and how optional Android/Jetty reflective paths could be bypassed if stubs aren’t retained. The prompt instructs me to choose \\\"no_action\\\" unless I uncover solid proof that extra setup is necessary. However, I’ve found some concrete information: AddAllCharsets for the native image relates to UTF-32 Charset.forName, and there are existing build comments. But wait, I’m not entirely sure if this is an environment or system property.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering guidance format**\\n\\nI need to provide guidance about environment, system properties, or test setup. It seems like I should avoid using an array format and stick to JSON instead. Also, I want to keep the response straightforward, so I’ll make sure not to include too much verbosity. It’s interesting how format choices can affect clarity, so this approach should help keep everything neatly organized!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"OkHttp 3.8.1 does not need an extra Maven dependency or Docker service; its meaningful metadata coverage depends on test-code/native-image setup for optional platform-reflection paths and charset initialization.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Retain or regenerate the local test stubs for Android, Conscrypt, dalvik CloseGuard, and Jetty ALPN classes when exercising okhttp3.internal.platform reflective code. Keep the native-image test build argument -H:+AddAllCharsets because okhttp3.internal.Util eagerly resolves UTF-32 charsets during static initialization. The javac failure is from OkHttp API drift: in 3.8.1 Util.intersect takes a Comparator as its first argument, not Class<String>.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Adding mockwebserver is useful for upstream-style HTTP integration tests but is not required for the existing metadata-oriented coverage and would be unnecessary setup for this compile fix.\",\n    \"If the optional platform stubs are omitted, tests may still compile but will miss the Android, dalvik CloseGuard, Conscrypt, and Jetty ALPN reflective paths that the existing metadata covers.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0341f5692ed173a6016a3eb8d9f6d88194a649c4621cf1e5cb\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1960, "output": 2062, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33206, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782495417147, "responseId": "resp_0341f5692ed173a6016a3eb8b9b4dc81948f78cb4e250e6600"}}
